Now I have a "exit" question dealilng with how exits are seen with a
browser
(through http://xxx:1180/bin/describe).  In an unmodified a9.02 database
the exit
names show up like this: "&gt;T2.  Here is what the html source file looks
like for the same section:

Visible Exits: &lt;a href="/bin/describe?target=&lt;$exit_frob, #[['prose,
[]], ['manager, $user_maddog], ['name, ['prop, "Test", "Test"]],
['source, $the_pit], ['dest, $place_2]]&gt;"&gt;Test&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a
href="/bin/describe?target=&lt;$exit_frob, #[['prose, []], ['manager,
$user_maddog], ['name, ['prop, "T2", "T2"]], ['source, $the_pit],
['dest, $place_3]]&gt;"&gt;T2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;hr size=1 noshade&gt;&lt;a href="/"&gt;the Cold Dark&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/body&gt;

Notice the $exit_frob after target.

Here are what the exits look like at cold.org:

Visible Exits: &lt;a href="/bin/describe?target=$place_334"&gt;the opening&lt;/a&gt;


 What fix do i need for this?

thanks,

frank

